Hi

The implementation answer is that grid::unit() calls as.numeric() on 
'x', which drops names.

The design answer is that having names on units was (naively) not 
considered in the original design.

The obstacle is that all functions that manipulate units would need to 
be made "names-aware".  That might be tricky for more complex units like ...

max(unit(1:3, "in"))

... though I guess the behaviour of numeric vectors could provide a 
role-model.

Paul

